ARPredir -- Just a simple ARP spoofing tool

Programmed by Bastian Ballmann
Last Update: 06.06.2004
Licensed under GPL

-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-

---:[ Requires

- Perl
- Tk module [ http://www.cpan.org ]


---:[ Disclaimer

THIS PROJECT WAS DEVELOPED FOR TESTING AND DEMONSTRATION PURPOSE ONLY! 
THE AUTHORS DONT FEEL RESPONSIBLE FOR ILLEGAL ABUSE OF THIS PIECE OF 
SOFTWARE AND WE ADVICE YOU TO USE IT LEGALLY AND DO NOT BREAK THE LAW!


---:[ Description

ARPredir is a simple ARP spoofing tool.
It contains a GUI frontend written in Perl/Tk.
This tool can implement a man-in-the-middle attack based on ARP cache 
poisoning. You can use it to spoof one way (tell one host that the ip
of another host points to your mac address) to spoof a whole connection
at once or to spoof all arp requests on a network.


---:[ Installation

If your system supports Perl just install the required modules and run
./arpredir.pl for the terminal version or ./arpredir.pl --gui to use the GUI 
version of the tool.


---[ Usage

Run ./arpredir.pl --help to get help

